dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Vrsac, sheet Y-18. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dc_description_s: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Vrsac. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Danube zone grid. Gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1949. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With Serb and Croat and Romanian glossaries. Corrected from intelligence reports up to May 1944. Compiled and drawn by War Office, 1944. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic area is designated as Yugoslavia it is Serbia and Motenegro.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1949.
